    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The Fellowship is a basic Archery deck.  Beef-up Aragorn and Legolas and watch the Arrows fly!  I would bid high to ensure that you can get out Aragorn.  After all you are starting with Sam so just remove those unwanted burdens.  Try to move as quickly has possible, this is my mistake.  If you are done with your first move and notice that Aragorn and Legolas are not seriously wounded and the next site is a sanctuary go ahead and unless of course they have alot of twilight to work with.  <br />
<br />
The Shadow side however is a little complicated.  My idea is to get as many burdens on the ring-bearer as possible using blade tip and thin and stretched, not nessicarely to corrupt him, but to have fun using Enquea&#39;s technique to kill of companions.  This is still in the testing phase for me so I would really like some advice if you could please.<br />
